cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with video classification, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for label inference, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with large-scale datasets, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the use of labels, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
